1.1.4 Implications for Sample Complexity

For parametric mismatch, DR requires N_{\text{sim}} = O(|\theta|/\epsilon^2) simulated trajectories for \epsilon-optimal robustness. For structural mismatch, covering the space of possible g_{\text{real}} via randomization requires sampling over function spaces: exponential complexity in state dimension or unmodeled phenomenon complexity.

Central thesis: Rather than randomize over all structural mismatches, explicitly discover and model the causal structure of the reality gap, then compensate in a sample-efficient manner.

