1.4 Mathematical Preliminaries

1.4.1 Causal Graphical Models and Interventions

Definition 1.3 (Directed Acyclic Graph). A DAG \mathcal{G} = (\mathbf{V}, \mathbf{E}) has nodes \mathbf{V} and edges \mathbf{E} \subseteq \mathbf{V} \times \mathbf{V} with no directed cycles. For v \in \mathbf{V}, parents \text{Pa}(v) = \{u: (u, v) \in \mathbf{E}\}, children \text{Ch}(v) = \{w: (v, w) \in \mathbf{E}\}, descendants \text{De}(v) are nodes reachable from $v$.

Definition 1.4 (Structural Causal Model). An SCM \mathcal{C} over \mathbf{V} consists of 1) DAG \mathcal{G} over \mathbf{V}, 2) independent exogenous \mathbf{U} = \{U_v\}_{v \in \mathbf{V}} with P(\mathbf{U}), 3) deterministic functions \mathbf{F} = \{f_v\}_{v \in \mathbf{V}} such that V_v := f_v(\text{Pa}(v), U_v). The SCM induces P(\mathbf{V}) satisfying the causal Markov condition: each variable independent of non-descendants given parents.

Definition 1.5 (Intervention). Intervention \text{do}(\mathbf{X} = \mathbf{x}) replaces structural equations for \mathbf{X} \subseteq \mathbf{V} with $X := x$. Resulting distribution: P(\mathbf{V} \mid \text{do}(\mathbf{X} = \mathbf{x})).

Definition 1.6 (Markov Equivalence). DAGs \mathcal{G}_1, \mathcal{G}_2 are Markov equivalent if they entail identical conditional independencies. The MEC [\mathcal{G}]_{\text{MEC}} contains all Markov equivalent DAGs. Causal discovery from observations alone recovers only MEC. Interventions break equivalences for full identifiability.

Definition 1.7 (Faithfulness). Distribution $P$ is faithful to DAG \mathcal{G} if every conditional independence in $P$ is entailed by Markov condition on \mathcal{G}. Ensures observed independencies reflect causal structure.

