1.4.3 Conformal Prediction

Definition 1.8 (Exchangeability). Z_1, \dots, Z_N exchangeable if joint distribution invariant under permutation: (Z_1, \dots, Z_N) \stackrel{d}{=} (Z_{\sigma(1)}, \dots, Z_{\sigma(N)}) for any permutation \sigma.

Definition 1.9 (Nonconformity Score). s(z) \in \mathbb{R} measures atypicality. Common choice: s(x,y) = \|\hat{y}(x) - y\|.

Split-Conformal Algorithm: Given calibration \mathcal{D}_{\text{cal}} = \{(X_i, Y_i)\}_{i=1}^{N} and test (X_{N+1}, Y_{N+1}) with Y_{N+1} unknown:
Compute s_i = s(X_i, Y_i) for i=1,\dots,N
For \alpha \in (0,1), compute quantile \hat{q}_{1-\alpha} = \text{Quantile}(\{s_i\}, \lceil (1-\alpha)(N+1) \rceil/N)
Prediction set: \hat{C}(X_{N+1}) = \{y: s(X_{N+1}, y) \leq \hat{q}_{1-\alpha}\}

Theorem 1.1 (Split-Conformal Coverage). If (X_1, Y_1), \dots, (X_{N+1}, Y_{N+1}) exchangeable, then \mathbb{P}(Y_{N+1} \in \hat{C}(X_{N+1})) \geq 1-\alpha. Guarantee is marginal, holds for any $N$, any predictor, any score.

For temporal robotics, staggered integral OCP provides long-run coverage for non-i.i.d. sequences. Conformal prediction with reachability combines finite-sample guarantees with set-based reachability to certify safety under learned dynamics and distribution shifts.

