CausalSim++ comprises six modules operating at 100Hz:

Module 1: Intervention-Supervised CRL Encoder. Maps observations o_t (RGB, depth, proprioception) to disentangled causal latent z_t via h_\psi pretrained in sim with GT z_t^\delta and finetuned on \mathcal{D}_{\text{real}} using interventional consistency. Latent z_t partitions into [z_t^{\text{phys}}, z_t^{\delta}].

