6.5 Calibration and Deployment Workflow

The full deployment workflow consists of offline calibration followed by online operation.

6.5.1 Offline Calibration (One-Time)

1. Collect Calibration Data: Using safe exploration policy \pi_{\text{safe}} (e.g., conservative PD control or teleoperation), collect N_{\text{cal}} \approx 15 trajectories on the real robot. Each trajectory consists of observations o_t, actions a_t, and (if available) ground-truth state from motion capture or joint encoders.
2. Train CRL Encoder: Run Algorithm 5.1 to finetune the simulation-pretrained encoder on real data.
3. Discover Causal Graph: Run Algorithm 2.1 on latent trajectories to obtain posterior P(\mathcal{C} \mid \mathcal{D}_{\text{cal}}).
4. Train Neural Residual: Train the causally masked neural network \phi_{\text{neural}} (Chapter 3) on calibration residuals.
5. Calibrate Conformal Quantile: Run Algorithm 4.2 to compute \hat{q}_{1-\alpha} for desired coverage 1-\alpha.
6. Export Models: Convert all neural networks to TensorRT/ONNX for deployment.

6.5.2 Online Operation

The system runs the real-time loop described in Section 6.2. The causal graph and neural residual weights are fixed during operation (though online adaptation is possible as discussed in Section 4.6). The safety monitor operates at full control rate, while the CRL encoder updates at camera frame rate.

