Appendix A: Lyapunov Stability Proof (Full Derivation)

This appendix provides the complete derivation of Theorem 3.2 (Exponential Stability under Causal Residuals). The proof follows the Lyapunov framework for mechanical systems with bounded disturbances.

Lyapunov Candidate:

V(e, \dot{e}) = \frac{1}{2}\dot{e}^\top M(q)\dot{e} + \frac{1}{2}e^\top K_p e + \alpha e^\top M(q)\dot{e}

Time Derivative:

\dot{V} = \dot{e}^\top M \ddot{e} + \frac{1}{2}\dot{e}^\top \dot{M} \dot{e} + e^\top K_p \dot{e} + \alpha \dot{e}^\top M \dot{e} + \alpha e^\top \dot{M} \dot{e} + \alpha e^\top M \ddot{e}

Using the closed-loop error dynamics:

M\ddot{e} = -C\dot{e} - K_p e - K_d \dot{e} + J_c^\top \lambda + \phi_{\text{neural}} - \Delta

where \Delta = M\ddot{q}_d + C\dot{q}_d + g(q) - \tau_{\text{ff}} represents bounded terms from the desired trajectory and gravity compensation.

Substitute and use skew-symmetry \dot{M} - 2C skew-symmetric:

\dot{V} = -\dot{e}^\top K_d \dot{e} + \dot{e}^\top (J_c^\top \lambda + \phi_{\text{neural}} - \Delta) + \alpha \dot{e}^\top M \dot{e} - \alpha e^\top (C\dot{e} + K_p e + K_d \dot{e}) + \alpha e^\top (J_c^\top \lambda + \phi_{\text{neural}} - \Delta) + \alpha e^\top \dot{M} \dot{e}

Group terms:

\dot{V} \leq -\dot{e}^\top (K_d - \alpha M) \dot{e} - \alpha e^\top K_p e - \alpha e^\top C \dot{e} - \alpha e^\top K_d \dot{e} + \alpha e^\top \dot{M} \dot{e} + (\dot{e} + \alpha e)^\top (J_c^\top \lambda + \phi_{\text{neural}} + \Delta)

Using bounds on M, C, \dot{M} and choosing \alpha sufficiently small, the quadratic terms in \dot{e} and e dominate. Specifically, let:

\lambda_{\min}(K_d) > \alpha \lambda_{\max}(M) + L \|J_c\|^2

where L is the Lipschitz constant of \phi_{\text{neural}}. Then there exists \beta > 0 such that:

\dot{V} \leq -\beta V + \gamma

where \gamma bounds the terms involving \lambda, \Delta. The exponential convergence follows from the comparison lemma. ∎

