7.6 Statistical Analysis Plan

7.6.1 Significance Testing

We will report 95% bootstrap confidence intervals for all primary metrics. For pairwise comparisons between CausalSim++ and baselines, we will use:

· Paired bootstrap test: Resample trials with replacement and compute the distribution of performance differences.
· Wilcoxon signed-rank test: Non-parametric test for paired samples, appropriate for success rates and other non-normal metrics.

7.6.2 Sample Size Justification

Each task-condition combination will be evaluated with N=30 independent trials. This sample size provides:

· 80% power to detect a 15% absolute difference in success rate (two-sided, \alpha=0.05)
· Sufficient data for reliable bootstrap confidence intervals

For calibration trajectories (used in causal discovery and residual training), we will evaluate sample efficiency by varying N_{\text{cal}} \in \{5, 10, 15, 20\} and measuring performance.

7.6.3 Multiple Comparisons Correction

When testing multiple hypotheses (e.g., comparing CausalSim++ against 8 baselines across 10 tasks), we will apply the Benjamini-Hochberg procedure to control the false discovery rate at 0.05.

