Chapter 8: Discussion, Limitations, and Future Work

This dissertation has introduced CausalSim++, a unified framework for zero-shot sim-to-real transfer that integrates causal discovery, differentiable contact dynamics, conformal safety filtering, and causal representation learning. In this final chapter, we synthesize the contributions, critically examine the limitations of the approach, and chart directions for future research. We conclude with a reflection on the broader implications of this work for the field of robot learning and for the deployment of autonomous systems in safety-critical applications.

